Done. Fresh-eyes notes added to the bottom of `src/blog/people/drafts/Brendan-Fraser.md`.

**Reviewed:** the Brendan Fraser Type 9 draft (a genuinely strong one — disciplined on formula, real critic pressure, a clean Venice bookend).

**The two biggest issues I flagged:**

1. **His real fatherhood is missing entirely** — and that's the exact hole the article is built to fill. The closer is the *Rental Family* metaphor ("a man hired to be someone's family"), but Fraser actually has three sons (eldest is autistic), and the lost-decade section names his divorce and his mother's death while leaving the kids out. A reader who knows him reads that as a dodge. Threading even one or two sentences about his sons into the back half would make the ending pay off against a real family instead of only a metaphorical one.

2. **The dramatic-actor range is smoothed off** — the draft rounds pre-2003 Fraser into pure beefcake (*George of the Jungle*, biceps, golden-retriever charm), but he did *School Ties*, *Gods and Monsters*, and was in *Crash*. The "audiences only saw the body" point gets *sharper*, not weaker, if you concede he showed depth early and got typecast anyway.

Smaller notes in the block: expand the *Doom Patrol*/"Brendanaissance" comeback bridge and the child-support/financial collapse; trim a light "noose" echo and a repeated "like a little kid." No body edits made, per the command.
